    "body": "I've had a play around with this today as when running tox (during the git submodule for `tests/fixtures`) my laptop would either crash or I'd get an error saying I didn't have enough disk space :disappointed:\r\n\r\nAs a workaround I've forked the `ethereum/execution-specs` repo, and created a branch without the `tests/fixtures` submodule. Then pointed the `install_requires` in _setup.cfg_ to that [branch](https://github.com/spencer-tb/execution-specs/tree/exec-spec-tests-tox).\r\n\r\nIts not the ideal solution but I can create a PR for this if its useful. I'm going to add a ` .git/workflow` to the forked git branch such that its kept up-to-date with upstream whilst ignoring the `tests/fixtures` submodules.",
